        <item>
            <title>1.8.2</title>
            <pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 21:12:17 +0900</pubDate>
            <link>https://github.com/Saqoosha/Canopy</link>
            <sparkle:version>30</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.8.2</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[### Bug Fixes
- Session list now includes directories whose names contain spaces (e.g. `Canopy Companion`). Sessions from such folders were silently dropped due to lossy path decoding; the launcher now reads the working directory straight from session metadata.
- Legacy session folders written by older CLI versions (which preserved `.` and spaces in folder names) are consulted alongside the current encoding, so `loadSessions(for:)` and message counts no longer miss them.
- Session metadata extraction uses lossy UTF-8 decoding so a 128KB buffer boundary landing inside a multibyte sequence (Japanese or other non-ASCII content) no longer drops the entire buffer.
]]></description>
